10: I've got more where that came from!
14: There! That should be the last of them.
17:
So much for scouting the place out. 
You've crushed every single monster 
in our path.
20:
Whoops! Didn't mean to hog the fun, 
kitten. My nose got the better of me.
22:
This Kaleidoscope of yours is full of 
surprises. An ever-changing dungeon, 
with secrets untold lurking in its 
unexplored depths.
23:
Whenever you tidy up that Lord of 
Shadows business and put me out of a 
job, I might have to come back.
24: I'd be here till the day I die!
27:
Oh, don't give me that look. A lady can 
dream of lifelong employment, can't 
she?
37:
I'm sorry, Nimbus. I underestimated 
the amount of time I'd take.
41:
I shoulda known better than to take 
you in the book store. Thought we'd be 
in there all day!
70:
Why, we're ruff-housing, of course! 
Care to join the dogpile?
78:
Wouldn't have pegged you as the type 
who's good with kids. I thought you 
only cared about fighting.
81:
Goodness, I'm a soldier, not a war-
monger.
84:
Hah. You're always lookin' for fights, 
though.
87:
That doesn't mean I can't appreciate 
some peace and tranquility off the 
battlefield.
89:
Children playing without a care in the 
world—that's how things SHOULD be.
...Even if it puts soldiers like me out of 
work.
93:
What will you do when there are no 
more battles to be fought—anywhere? 
People'll figure out what's down in the 
Kaleidoscope's depths eventually.
97:
When there are no more battles to be 
fought, eh? Optimistic, but certainly 
has a ring to it.
99:
I'm sure I'll be long dead by then. You 
either die a hero—or live long enough 
to see yourself become the villain.
107:
What, you sure you wouldn't rather be 
the world's new supervillain?
111:
Ahahaha! Tempting, but no, I'd rather 
fight for peace than against it.
114:
Come now, Stella sweetie. It was just 
a what-if." I'm not going anywhere.
116:
How about you, kitten? Need a little 
scratch behind the ears?
122:
I didn't mean to frighten you, Stella 
sweetie. I'll be all right.
123:
I'm hardly new to the soldier business, 
and I knew what I was getting myself 
into from the start.
124:
I'm fighting for a world that doesn't 
need people like me.
...And the sooner it comes, the better!
127:
Fighting for a world that won't need 
you... Sounds pretty complex.
129:
Perhaps, but I needn't worry about it 
for a while yet! I was right to come join 
you lot—never a dull day.
130:
You have my deepest gratitude, 
Nimbus Whitetail.
137:
Now, we'd best be moving! I'm sure Alk 
is whipping up supper as we speak. 
Come along, now, children!
